{"word":"ἐφέζομαι","slug":"ἐφέζομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐφέζομαι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <el>ἐφέζεσθαι</el>) </el><p/><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to sit upon</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>;—also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>; and <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to sit by</i> or <i>near</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}